faqItems.title: I Can’t Connect
faqItems.text:
Before Starting. Please make sure that you are meeting the following terms:
-	You are connected to the internet (WiFi \ Mobile Carrier 2G \ 3G \ 4G)

-	Your iOS version is at least 8 or later

-	Your device is using Apple’s official iOS software and it’s not jailbroken

-	A 3rd party app is not interfering with Internet Settings such as antivirus, firewall, TV Streamer etc.

-	Please make sure you are running the latest version of the app. To make sure you are running the latest version, please check 
Please Follow the following Steps:

Clear your iOS device cookies and cache files, by tapping 'Settings > Safari > Clear History and Website Data,' then reboot your device.

1.	Open HotSpot VPN, choose your preferred location and tap "Connect"

2.	Open your device's Settings and turn Airplane Mode ON and then OFF. Then go back to HotSpot VPN and change its status to Disconnected

3.	In the HotSpot VPN app, tap Change Location, and then tap ‘Optimal’ Server and then tab Connect. After Connecting to ‘Optimal’ server, choose a different location with the closest data center to your location. (i.e If you are in United Stated, Choose a server in United States. If in Europe, Choose a server in Europe, etc..)

4.	Go to your iOS device's Settings, scroll down until you see the HotSpot VPN application and Turn off Background app refresh. Wait until it’s "OFF" and then turn it back to "ON."

5.	Last step - Just as a test, try to connect to different network temporarily (for example, if you were connected to Wi-Fi, try connecting to your mobile data network or vice versa), then open HotSpot VPN and tap Connect

If the issue persists, please uninstall the current version and download it again the %[following link here.] 

We suggest you visit our ‘Which Server Should I pick’ article that might improve the service significantly for you.

If none of the solutions worked for you, You are more than welcome to contact us directly through our app’s %[Contact Us] and our support team will be glad to assist!

faqItems.title: Why shouldn’t I use free VPN’s?
faqItems.text:
VPN servers has (high) costs. Especially servers that should provide you with decent speed and security. When you are surfing through VPN, each kilobyte of surfing reflects a cost for it’s provides, just like an internet supplier. This is where you should ask yourself how come a free VPN is free. 

The flat truth is that Free VPNs are dangerous. They might and probably will share your data with 3rd parties in order to make money or for any other reason. Also, your data is most likely to be stored somewhere, and you get no guarantees that your data, surfing history and personal information will not be used or sold. By presenting ads Free VPNs simply cannot cover VPN costs, even by showing a lot of ads every session. So there might be two scenarios:

1. The servers are not secured, they are cheap and the speed and performance will perform poor and slow service. 
2. Your data is being stored and might be sold to 3rd parties in order to cover the expenses.

HotSpot VPN provides you with free VPN data for limited time so you can enjoy our product and experience the benefits of premium VPN yourself. We provide the best servers for our users, covering you completely and making sure that you are getting the fastest and most secured VPN. You can trust our trusted company for not storing or sharing your personal data anywhere and that you will be getting the best and most secured service out there.
